40|$|The {{atypical}} antipsychotic drugs (AAPDs) have markedly {{enhanced the}} treatment <b>of</b> <b>schizophrenias</b> but their use has been hindered {{by the major}} weight gain elicited by some AAPDs. We report that orexigenic AAPDs potently and selectively activate hypothalamic AMP-kinase, an action abolished in mice with deletion of histamine H 1 receptors. These findings may afford a means of developing more effective therapeutic agents and {{provide insight into the}} hypothalamic regulation of food intake...|$|R
